c.org/post/west-virginia-community-organizer-jumps-2020-gubernatorial-race#stream/0 |website=WV Public Broadcasting |accessdate=August 30, 2019 |date=November 27, 2018}}</ref>\n*[[Ron Stollings]], state senator<ref>{{cite web |last1=Jenkins |first1=Jeff |title=Stollings to run for governor |url=http://wvmetronews.com/2019/09/23/stollings-to-run-for-governor/ |website=WV MetroNews |publisher=WV MetroNews |accessdate=23 September 2019}}</ref>\n\n====Declined====\n* [[Booth Goodwin]], former [[United States Attorney]] and candidate for Governor of West Virginia in [[2016 West Virginia gubernatorial election#Democratic primary|2016]]<ref name=\"Dems\">{{cite web|last1=Adams|first1=Steven Allen|title=Tis the election season again|url=https://www.journal-news.net/journal-news/tis-the-election-season-again/article_2333ae6a-0ed5-53a7-9d80-31b63f3896c8.html|work=The Journal|date=December 3, 2018|accessdate=December 5, 2018}}</ref>\n*[[Joe Manchin]], incumbent U.S. Senator and former Governor of West Virginia<ref>{{cite news|url = https://www.politico.com/story/2019/09/03/joe-manchin-wont-run-for-governor-of-west-virginia-1479602|work = [[Politico]]|title = Joe Manchin won't run for governor of West Virginia|date = September 3, 2019|accessdate = September 3, 2019|last = Levine|first = Marianne}}</ref>\n\n=== Endorsements ===\n{{Endorsements box\n|title=Stephen Smith\n|list=\n;Federal politicians\n* [[Elizabeth Warren]], U.S. Senator (D-MA)<ref>{{cite web |last1=McElhinny |first1=Brad |title=Elizabeth Warren pitches an early endorsement for Stephen Smith's campaign for governor |url=http://wvmetronews.com/2019/09/09/elizabeth-warren-pitches-an-early-endorsement-for-stephen-smiths-campaign-for-governor/ |website=WV MetroNews |date=September 9, 2019 |quote=\u201cI\u2019m proud to endorse Stephen\u2019s bid for governor, and his team\u2019s efforts to run candidates up and down the ballot,\u201d Warren stated.}}</ref> \n;Organizations\n* 90 for 90<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.90for90.org/2020-candidates-west-virginia|title=2020 Candidates West Virginia|website=90 for 90|accessdate=March 28, 2020}}</ref>\n* Blue America<ref name=\"herald dispatch stephen smith\">{{cite web|url=https://www.herald-dispatch.com/elections/wv_candidates/w-va-governor-candidate-stephen-smith-d/article_47888dae-6188-11ea-814f-2f7f2d8c3d3d.html|title=W.Va. Governor candidate: Stephen Smith (D)|journal=The Herald Dispatch|date=March 8, 2020|accessdate=March 28, 2020}}</ref>\n* More than Addiction<ref name=\"herald dispatch stephen smith\"/>\n* [[People for the American Way]] - Next Up<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.pfaw.org/next-up-victory-fund/candidates|title=Next Up Endorses Young Progressive Candidates|website=People for the American Way|accessdate=March 28, 2020}}</ref>\n* [[Progressive Change Campaign Committee]]<ref>{{cite web |title=Join the Bold Progressive Movement!|url=https://www.boldprogressives.org/candidates/ |website=Progressive Change Campaign Committee (BoldProgressives.org)}}</ref>\n* Rise Up West Virginia<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.riseupwv.org/endorsements|title=2020 Endorsements|website=Rise Up West Virginia|accessdate=March 28, 2020}}</ref>\n* [[Working Families Party]] - national<ref>{{cite web|url=https://workingfamilies.org/2020/01/join-us-sunday-for-the-next-wfp-assembly/|title=Join us Sunday for the next WFP Assembly|website=Working Families Party|date=January 24, 2020|accessdate=March 28, 2020}}</ref>\n* [[Working Families Party]] - West Virginia chapter\n* [[Planned Parenthood]] Votes! South Atlantic <ref>{{cite web |title=Planned Parenthood Votes! South Atlantic Announces Election Endorsements, including Stephen Smith for Governor|url=https://www.plannedparenthoodaction.org/planned-parenthood-votes-south-atlantic/press-room/planned-parenthood-votes-south-atlantic-announces-election-endorsements-including-stephen-smith-for-governor |website=Planned Parenthood Action Fund (PlannedParenthoodAction.org)}}</ref>\n}}\n{{Endorsements box\n|title=Ben Salango\n|list=\n;Statewide politicians\n* [[Gaston Caperton]], former [[Governor of West Virginia]]<ref>{{cite web| last1=Adams| first1=Steven Allen| title=Another endorsement for @BenSalango| url=https://twitter.com/stevenadamswv/status/1207331362434215938| publisher=Twitter| date=December 18, 2019}}</ref>\n;Labor unions\n* [[West Virginia AFL\u2013CIO]]<ref>{{cite web |title=2020 Primary Election Cope Endorsements |url=https://wvaflcio.org/legislative-and-political/2020-primary-election-cope-endorsements.html |website=West Virginia AFL-CIO |language=en-gb}}</ref>\n}}\n{{Endorsements box\n|title=Ron Stollings\n|list=\n;Organizations\n* [[West Virginia Education Association]], <ref>{{cite web| title=WVEA-PAC has made their recommendations for the May Primary Election.| url=https://twitter.com/WVEAnews/status/1244720062738685952| publisher=Twitter| date=March 30, 2020}}</ref>\n}}\n\n===Polling===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:90%;text-align:center;\"\n|- valign=bottom\n! Poll source\n! Date(s)<br>administered\n! Sample<br>size{{efn|name=key}}\n! Margin<br>of error\n! style=\"width:100px;\"| Ben<br>Salango\n! style=\"width:100px;\"| Stephen<br>Smith\n! style=\"width:100px;\"| Ron<br>Stollings\n! Other\n! Undecided\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"| [http://wvmetronews.com/2019/12/13/west-virginia-poll-democratic-primary-is-up-for-grabs-with-most-still-undecided/ Research America/MetroNews]\n| Dec 4-10, 2019\n| 220 (LV)\n| \u2013\n| 17.7%\n| {{party shading/Democratic}}|'''21.4%'''\n| 18.6%\n| 4.1%{{efn|Cecil Silva with 1.8%; Jody Murphy with 1.4%; Edwin Vanover with 0.5%}}\n| {{party shading/Undecided}}|'''42.3%'''\n|} \n\n===Results===\n{{Election box begin no change\n| title = Democratic primary results\n}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link no change\n| candidate = Doug Hughes\n| party = Democratic Party (United States)\n| votes = \n| percentage = \n}}\n{{Election box  candidate with party link no change\n| candidate = Jody Murphy\n